jayree:manifest:cleanup.description:
removes those tags from a manifest file that are present in a second manifest file
Use this command to remove components or metadata types from a manifes file.
If the 'cleanup' manifest file (--file) doesn't exist, a template file is created, which can then be modified.

loglevel.name: loglevel
loglevel.description: logging level for this command invocation

file.name: file
file.description: path to the second 'cleanup' manifest file

jayree:manifest:generate.description:
generate a complete manifest file form the specified org
Use this command to generate a manifest file based on an existing org.

loglevel.name: loglevel
loglevel.description: logging level for this command invocation

targetusername.name: targetusername
targetusername.description: username or alias for the target org; overrides default target org

apiversion.name: apiversion
apiversion.description: override the api version used for api requests made by this command

quickfilter.name: quickfilter
quickfilter.description: csv separated list of metadata type, member or file names to filter on

matchwholeword.name: matchwholeword
matchwholeword.description: enable 'match whole word' for the quickfilter

includeflowversions.name: includeflowversions
includeflowversions.description: include flow versions as with api version 43.0

jayree:manifest:git:diff.description:
create a manifest and destructiveChanges manifest using 'git diff' data
Use this command to create a manifest and destructiveChanges manifest file based on the difference (git diff) of two git refs.

You can use all ways to spell <commit> which are valid for 'git diff'.
(See https://git-scm.com/docs/git-diff)
examples: uses the changes between two arbitrary <commit>
uses the changes on the branch containing and up to the second <commit>, starting at a common ancestor of both <commit>.
uses the diff of what is unique in branchB (REF2) and unique in branchA (REF1)
uses the diff of what is unique in branchB (REF2)

loglevel.name: loglevel
loglevel.description: logging level for this command invocation

outputdir.name: outputdir
outputdir.description: directory to save the created manifest files

destructivechangesonly.name: destructivechangesonly
destructivechangesonly.description: create a destructiveChanges manifest only (package.xml will be empty)

args.name: ref2
args.description: commit or branch to compare to the base commit
